cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use afair in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "afair: a user-owned, vendor-neutral memory vault for AI assistants"
abstract: >-
  afair is a self-hostable memory substrate for AI agents, exposed over the
  Model Context Protocol. It stores an append-only, content-addressed event log
  that any MCP client can read and write through three frozen verbs (remember,
  recall, observe), with cold-path agents that extract, link, and synthesize over
  the same substrate.
type: software
authors:
